    q: "Do you wear clothes in a sauna blanket?",
    a: "Yes - it is recommended. Wearing long sleeves and leggings (or using the blanket's washable insert) keeps sweat off the heating layer, protects your skin from direct contact with the hot surface, and makes cleanup far easier. Loose, breathable cotton works best; avoid lying bare directly against the inner surface, and never sit on the controller or cords.",
  },
