    q: "Do sauna blankets use a lot of electricity?",
    a: "No - they are one of the cheapest ways to sweat. A typical blanket draws roughly 0.5-1 kW, so a 30-45 minute session uses well under 1 kWh, a few cents at usual electricity rates. That low running cost, plus a low purchase price and almost no install, is a big part of why blankets are the easiest entry point into home infrared.",
